# Dineros.cc — Overview

Dineros.cc is a Nuxt 4 + TypeScript application for predictive budgeting, real‑time spending optimization, and simplified accounting. It combines a feature‑rich frontend with a server (Nuxt Nitro API routes) and a companion microservice. The system includes a forecasting engine, Plaid banking integration, encryption-at-rest, queue processing, and extensive automated tests.

## Purpose

- Help users plan and track personal finances across multiple accounts and categories
- Forecast balances and cash flow using a modular forecasting engine
- Integrate with Plaid for secure transaction and balance sync
- Provide admin tools, notifications, and audit/logging facilities

## Tech stack

- Application framework: Nuxt 4 (Vue 3), TypeScript
- ORM: Prisma (MySQL 8)
- Cache/queues: Redis, BullMQ
- Messaging and integrations: NATS (client present), Plaid, Postmark, OpenAI
- Testing: Vitest (unit/integration), Playwright (E2E), CodeQL (security), SonarQube (optional workflow)
- CI/CD: GitHub Actions (build, push to GCR, GKE deployment), K8s templates under .deploy/
- Encryption: prisma-field-encryption (field-level), RSA/JWT services

## Audience

- Core contributors implementing features in the Nuxt app, API routes, and services
- Backend engineers modifying Prisma schema, migrations, queues, and integrations
- SRE/DevOps maintaining Docker/K8s, secrets, and CI/CD pipelines
- Test engineers maintaining Vitest and Playwright suites
- AI agents (Cursor-style) following project rules under .cursor/

## Key capabilities

- Forecasting engine (server/services/forecast/*) with rich test suite
- Extensive domain: budgets, accounts, registers, reoccurrences, reconciliation, bills, savings goals, crypto wallets, notifications
- Field-level encryption with re-encryption tooling and key rotation workflows
- Microservice to support specialized operations and key-rotation/migration flows

